{"word":"H3529 - כְּבָר - Kᵉbâr - keb-awr' - Chebar","slug":"H3529","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כְּבָר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Kᵉbâr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>keb-awr'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chebar"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>כּבר</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>kebâr</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>keb-awr'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Chebar = \"far-off\" <ol><li>a Babylonian river near which many Israelite exiles settled; maybe the 'Habor' or the 'Royal Canal' of Nebuchadnezzar</li></ol> <p />Origin: the same as <a href=\"#/H3528\">H3528</a> <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0947 - kabar\">947d</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3524\">H3524</a>, <a href=\"#/H3527\">H3527</a>, <a href=\"#/H3528\">H3528</a>, <a href=\"#/H3530\">H3530</a>, <a href=\"#/H4342\">H4342</a>"}]}